Definition: the legal status of a person who is alive but who has been deprived of the rights and privileges of a citizen or a member of society
Example: the legal status of one sentenced to life imprisonment
Synonyms: legal_status, noun, group, law, c, the, legal, status, of, a, person, who, is, alive, but, has, been, deprived, rights, and, privileges, citizen, or, member, society, one, sentenced, to, life, imprisonment
Category: noun.state
